## Print Order Recommendation

Print in this order to catch fit issues early before committing to longer prints:

1. **Parts 5 & 6** (clips) — quick functional test, verify PETG settings
2. **Part 3** (ear accent) — fast, warm up your PLA
3. **Part 1** (side housing) — test fit against Part 7 footprint
4. **Parts 4 & 8** (face/chest panels) — slow detailed prints, do overnight
5. **Part 2** (base plate) — large flat print, straightforward
6. **Part 7** (main body) — save the longest print for last, confirm all other parts fit first

---

## Post-Processing

- **Remove supports** with flush cutters before assembling
- **Sand seam lines** on visible surfaces with 220 → 400 grit
- **Test-fit all parts dry** before any glue or hardware
- **Cable routing:** Route wires through Part 7 body channels before closing the assembly
- **Painting:** Prime with grey filler primer; acrylic paint adheres well to PLA and PETG

